title: Variable Inspector
modified: 20260331215234581

!! Introduction

The Variable Inspector shows all variables in scope at a specific element. Open it via ''Inspect variables'' in the [[Context Menu]]. Multiple inspectors can be open simultaneously, each with its own colour.

[img[screenshot-variable-inspector]]

!! Panel Layout

* ''Coloured top border'' — each inspector gets a unique colour from a rotating palette of 6 colours (blue, green, orange, purple, yellow, cyan)
* ''Header'' — colour dot, title showing variable count, filter input, link button, close button
* ''Variable list'' — scrollable list grouped by source tiddler

!! Variable Types

Each variable is shown with a coloured type badge:

|! Badge |! Type |! Description |
|! `widget` |Widget definition |Purple badge |
|! `fn` |Function definition |Dark red badge |
|! `proc` |Procedure definition |Green badge |
|! `macro` |Macro definition |Brown badge |
|! `def` |Definition with parameters |Blue badge |
|! `var` |Simple variable |Gray badge |

!! Variable Display

Each row shows:

* ''Type badge'' — coloured label indicating the variable type
* ''Variable name'' — in cyan
* ''Parameters'' — for definitions: `(param1:default, param2)`
* ''Value'' — truncated at 80 characters with ellipsis for long values
* ''Macro substitution'' — for macros, the evaluated body is shown with colour-coded substitutions:
** ''Green'' — matched variable substitutions
** ''Red'' — missing variable substitutions

!! Grouping

Variables are grouped by their ''source tiddler'', with separator lines showing the tiddler title (e.g., `── $:/core/macros/CSS`). Local variables (no source tiddler) appear first under `── local scope`.

!! Filtering

The filter input supports smart matching:

* ''Type keywords'' (`var`, `macro`, `proc`, `def`, `fn`, `widget`) — match against the type badge only
* ''Other terms'' — match against variable name or value (case-insensitive)
* ''Local variables'' (no source tiddler) — any term matches (OR logic)
* ''Non-local variables'' (from tiddlers) — all terms must match (AND logic)

!! Action Buttons

Buttons appear on hover for each variable row:

|! Button |! When shown |! Action |
|! Preview (eye) |Tiddler references |Toggles an inline preview of the tiddler content below the row |
|! Open (link) |Tiddler references |Navigates to the tiddler in the story river |
|! View (eye) |Definitions with body |Toggles the full definition preview with syntax |
|! Evaluate (eye) |Function definitions |Shows the filter evaluation result or error |

!! Preview Features

* Previews are limited to ''3.6em height'' by default with a fade gradient
* ''Click to expand/collapse'' the full content
* Preview state persists for that inspector session

!! Linked Panels

The ''link button'' (&#x1F517;) controls synchronisation across all open inspector panels:

* ''Linked'' (default) — filter text, panel size, and preview toggles are synced across all inspectors
* ''Unlinked'' — each panel operates independently

!! Origin Highlighting

* The inspected element gets a ''persistent coloured outline'' matching the panel's colour
* Opening the panel ''blinks'' the element 3 times in red, then applies the steady colour
* Each panel uses a different colour, so multiple inspectors can highlight different elements simultaneously

!! Live Updates

* Variables are ''re-collected'' after each TiddlyWiki page refresh (`th-page-refreshed` hook)
* The variable list updates automatically while maintaining filter state
* If the origin element is removed from the DOM (e.g., by a TW re-render), the panel shows a ''&#x26A0; disconnected'' badge and attempts to relocate the element

!! Keyboard

* ''Escape'' — closes the panel when the mouse is over it

